  "doc_id": "4967",
  "text": "The large number of samples representing the major GTs in this study allowed the direct comparison of RAS prevalence between GTs, particularly between GT1a and GT3a (Table S1 ). Notable differences detected in this analysis included NS3 Q80K, which was associated with GT1a samples, and NS5B N142T, which was associated with GT3a. Understanding these genotypic differences is crucial for future therapies where pan-genotypic regimens are the ultimate goal. Our analysis has also demonstrated differences in the prevalence of some RASs within the same genotype, but across different geographic regions. The geographical association of the NS5B RAS, N142T, has not been previously reported, which may be due to the lack of large-scale analyses of GT3a-associated RASs. This substitution has been associated with resistance to some HCV NIs, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] but had no effect on the potency of sofosbuvir in vitro [CITATION_3] or treatment outcome in vivo. [CITATION_4] The geographic spread of NS3 Q80K has been well documented, reaching levels of 48% in North American GT1a isolates, between 0% and 19%",
